  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "The Beacon API `v2.4.0` defines the [getLiveness endpoint](https://ethereum.github.io/beacon-APIs/#/Validator/getLiveness) as following:\r\n\r\n- **Verb:** POST\r\n- **Endpoint:**  `/eth/v1/validator/liveness/{epoch}`\r\n- **Body example:** \r\n```\r\n[\"1\", \"42\", \"1664\"]\r\n```\r\n(List of indexes)\r\n\r\nHowever, the Teku implements the [getLiveness endpoint](https://docs.teku.consensys.net/api#tag/Experimental/operation/postValidatorLiveness) in a slightly different way:\r\n- **Verb:** POST (same)\r\n- **Endpoint:**  `/eth/v1/validator/liveness/{epoch}` (same)\r\n- **Body example:** \r\n```\r\n{\r\n   \"indices\": [\r\n      \"1\",\r\n      \"42\",\r\n      \"1663\"\r\n   ]\r\n}\r\n```\r\n(Map with `indices` as key and with a list of indexes as value)\r\n\r\nIs there any specific reason not to conform to the specification?\r\nIf no, would it be possible to adapt it?\r\nIf you don't want do break retro-compatibility, I guess it's possible for the endpoint to accept both current Teku body and ETH beacon API specification body.",
